AusBus 2016 Vuelta Recap

19 August 2017

Introduction

With the 2017 Vuelta a Espaa set to commence wheels rolling tonight, its perhaps a good time to reflect on our performance twelve months earlier.

With 14 teams there was the opportunity for 9 unique teams and 81 riders in total. However the short list of favoured athletes in each category ultimately led us to select our squads from only 49 of the 198 riders starting the team time trial to Castrelo de Mio on the 20th of August, 2016.

The most popular rider was Columbian Johan Esteban Chaves with 6 of us selecting the always smiling Orica team member to do battle on Spanish roads.

Overall Team Performance

At the end of a tightly fought three week battle Steves safety first helmets took top step on the podium by a comfortable margin over Billys squad.

Individual Stage Performance

Steves team emerged in a controlling fashion from about Stage 7 and didnt look like relinquishing the lead for the remainder of the race.

Steves selection of big scoring Quintana and Valverde were differentiators for his squad.
